```js
const helmet = require('helmet');
app.use(helmet());
```

### 3. ⚠️ No Global Error Handler
Unhandled errors will crash the process or return stack traces to clients. Add a catch-all error middleware **last**:
```js
// 404 handler
app.use((req, res) => {
  res.status(404).json({ error: 'Not found' });
});

// Global error handler
app.use((err, req, res, next) => {
  console.error(err.stack); // log internally only
  res.status(err.status || 500).json({
    error: process.env.NODE_ENV === 'production'
      ? 'Internal server error'
      : err.message   // only expose details in dev
  });
});
```

### 4. 🚦 No Rate Limiting
The `/users` endpoint (and any future routes) are open to abuse. Add basic rate limiting:
