app.use(express.json({ limit: '10kb' })); // Also limits payload size (DoS protection)
app.use(express.urlencoded({ extended: false }));

// Example validated route
app.get('/users', [
  query('page').optional().isInt({ min: 1 }).toInt(),
], (req, res) => {
  const errors = validationResult(req);
  if (!errors.isEmpty()) return res.status(400).json({ errors: errors.array() });
  // ...
});
```

---

## ℹ️ Low / Informational

### 8. No Error Handling Middleware (OWASP A05)

**Finding:** Express's default error handler will emit stack traces to the client in development mode. If `NODE_ENV` is ever unset or misconfigured, this leaks internal file paths and logic.

```js
